JDK ->  JRE + JVM + others

JDK → Used by developers to write, compile, and run Java programs.
JRE → Used by users to run Java programs.
JVM → Actually executes the compiled Java bytecode.

JDK = Development Kit (JRE + tools).
JRE = Runtime Environment (JVM + libraries).
JVM = Executes Java bytecode.
JIT = Improves performance by compiling bytecode to native machine code during execution.
JAR = Packages Java applications into a single file.
JDBC = Connects Java programs to databases.


Interpreter (Simple Definition):
    An interpreter is a program that reads your code and executes it one instruction at a time, instead of converting the entire program into machine code beforehand.
    example : 🎤 Speaker says one sentence.
               🗣️ Interpreter immediately translates that sentence.
               🎤 Speaker says the next sentence.
               🗣️ Interpreter translates it.
    The interpreter works line by line, not all at once.
        System.out.println("Hello");
        System.out.println("World");


