Hash
    -> easy to understand, its one way
    -> it given random data
    -> converting data into an integer value
    -> it can store and retrieve efficiently
        SHA256


HashSet
    -> Contains unique elements, no duplicates
    -> inserting -> O(1)     almost constant time
    -> searching -> O(1)
    -> there is no index
    -> can't Sort


PriorityQueue
    -> it's min heap
    -> always removes the highest-priority element first.
    -> By default, the smallest element has the highest priority (min-heap).

    2 types
        1. min heap -> smallest element is always at the root(first position).
        2. max heap -> largest element is always at the root(first position).



